This article is about communications systems in Anguilla.

Telephone

Telephones - main lines in use: 6,200 (2002)
country comparison to the world: 212

Telephones - mobile cellular: 1,800 (2002)
country comparison to the world: 211

Telephone system:
Domestic: Modern internal telephone system
International: EAST CARIBBEAN FIBRE SYSTEM ECFS (cable system)
 microwave radio relay to island of Saint Martin (Guadeloupe and Netherlands Antilles)

Mobile Phone (GSM)

Mobile Phone Operators:
 Cable & Wireless (Anguilla) Ltd. - GSM 850 and 1900 MHz with Island-wide coverage 
 Weblinks - [http://www.weblinks.ai]

Mobiles: ? (2007)

Radio

Radio broadcast stations: AM 3, FM 7, shortwave 0 (2007)

Radios: 3,000 (1997)

Television

Television broadcast stations: 1 (1997)

Televisions: 1,000 (1997)

Internet

Internet country code: .ai (Top level domain)

Internet Service Providers (ISPs): 3 (Cable & Wireless - [http://www.anguillanet.com], Weblinks - [http://www.weblinks.ai], Caribbean Cable Communications - [http://www.caribcable.com] )

Internet hosts: 205 (2008)
country comparison to the world: 177

Internet: users: 3,000 (2002)
country comparison to the world: 206
